\begin_layout Enumerate
So when I graduated, I got graduate school offers from Cambridge and Oxford,
 but I also got the Duke offer.
 So I think, if I do graduate school in UK, I will probably stay in UK forever.
 So I decided, if I really want to come to America, this is time! 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Why First National Bank of Omaha
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
My original goal is to apply Finance PhD.
 So I applied the five or three of the top 20 schools, but it turned out
 that the admission of Finance PhD is super competitive, and normally they
 just enroll 2-3 people each year.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
So you see I was over-confident about my self at that time.
 AND when it came to 2013 March, I got rejections from all of those schools.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
So I say if I cannot stay in academia, let's try Industry.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Why change from Policy to Risk 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Because one guy who worked on loss forecasting left, and the manager in
 loss forecasting approached me to see why I like to move.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
I say why not.
 It is always good to try some new things and get challenged.
 You know when you stay in one area too long, you become more and more comfortab
le with your work, and thus your learning curve gets flatter and flatter,
 and you slowly loose your passion.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
I think the ideal situation is, you keep yourself being challenged, learning
 and trying new things.
 That's how you advance in your career.
 
\end_layout

